    <h1>Growth and perspective</h1>
    <p>
        As an adrenaline junkie, flipping and twisting mid-air and 70 feet above water is something I was born for…and a natural fit with the BYU Cosmo and Dunk team. This was such a fun way to do exciting things, promote the university and serve the community whether at sporting events or charitable visits at the hospital. After one too many trampoline bounces, I woke up one morning with tingling pains and debilitating aches down my back and legs that ironically sent me to the hospital with two bulging discs. Whereas just prior, I was in full stride with physical and academic goals, my work to become an elite athlete was met with an inability to tie my own shoes. I felt discouraged and hopeless as doctors predicted a new life of limitations. My nightly Hail Mary’s that I’d wake up pain-free the next day were fruitless. The energetic and dynamic life-style I had lived meant everything to me, and I was being told those days were in the past. Instead of accepting this as reality, I dug deep and committed to ten months of intense physical therapy to persevere through pain, thrive in the face of adversity and regain my health. This defining journey has taught me invaluable lessons of resilience, perspective to my identity and purpose and insight to others’ challenges. I am grateful for this trial, as what I have learned and who I have become is far greater than the challenge itself.
    </p>
